President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Drew B. Tipton of Texas to serve as a Judge on the United States District Court for the Southern District of Texas. Tipton is currently a partner at Baker Hostetler, LLP in Houston, where he specializes in complex labor and employment and trade secret litigation. Before joining Baker Hostetler, Tipton practiced law with Marek, Griffin, & Knaupp, LLP and Littler Mendelson, PC. He also served in the United States Marine Corps Reserve for 5 years. Tipton clerked for Judge John D. Rainey of the United States District Court for the Southern District of Texas after graduating from law school. He holds a B.A. from Texas A&M University and a J.D. from South Texas College of Law Houston.